physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and oriented, no acute distress. HEENT: Anicteric, mucous membranes moist. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/gallops/rubs. Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes/rales/ronchi. Abdominal: Right upper quadrant tenderness to palpation, positive Murphy's sign, soft, nondistended. Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused.
